C:\Data\Nucleus_Dev\Vostok_ACU_A\source\Category\Application\acu\Tasks\DoorOpeningSystemPush\DoorOpeningSystemPush.c
      1          /**
      2           *  @file		DoorOpeningSystemPush.c
      3           *
      4           *  @brief		A task that implements the sequence to push out the DOS pin
      5           *
      6           *  @details    Door Opening System (briefly DOS) is a device used to assist with the drying by opening the door of the dishwasher
      7           *  			releasing the moisture out of the tub at selected moment given by the cycle design.
      8           *  			Door Opening System Push Task shall be activated in the point of the cycle when the DOS pin has to be extracted.
      9           *  			No Deactivate Task call is needed, the task automatically deactivate itself when it is completed.
     10           *  			The Push sequence consists of 3 sequential steps, whose duration is specified by setting file parameters:
     11           *  			- First On: the DOS output is driven on.
     12           *  			- Off: the DOS output is driven off.
     13           *  			- Second On: the DOS output is driven on.
     14           *  			This sequence is processed by the DOS device controller to push out the device pin.
     15           *
     16           */
     17          
